'''Yang Fire Rooster also known as дЄБйЕЙ''' (hinototori, teika no tori, teiyuu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ}}.

It is the 34th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingshen|ja|дЄЩзФ≥}} and followed by {{ill|Wuxu|ja|жИКжИМ}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|зБЂ}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|еНБдЇМжФѓ}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|йЕЙ}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|йЗС}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ}}) (i.e. Fire overcomes Metal).

