It is the 34th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingshen|ja|дЄЩзФ≥|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Wuxu|ja|жИКжИМ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|зБЂ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|еНБдЇМжФѓ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|йЕЙ|1=Rooster (zodiac)|lt=Rooster (йЕЙ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|йЗС|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) (i.e. Fire overcomes Metal).

