It is the 34th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Bingshen|ja|дЄЩзФ≥|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Wuxu|ja|жИКжИМ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Tei|ja|дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|зБЂ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|еНБдЇМжФѓ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|йЕЙ|1=Rooster (zodiac)|2=ja|3=йЕЙ|4=fr|5=Coq (astrologie chinoise)|6=nl|7=Haan (astrologie)|lt=Rooster (йЕЙ)|1=Rooster (zodiac)|lt=Rooster (йЕЙ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|йЗС|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) (i.e. Fire overcomes Metal).

